# Git Commit Specification

Before writing any commit message, read `docs/git-commit-spec.md` and follow it exactly.

Summary:

`<type>(<scope>): <Chinese subject>`

- Allowed types: `feat`, `fix`, `perf`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `style`, `chore`, `revert`.
- Scope must come from the Vela UI scope list in `docs/git-commit-spec.md`.
- Scope must be lowercase kebab-case.
- Do not use Chinese, PascalCase, camelCase, or file-location scopes.
- There must be one space after the colon.
- Header must be 72 characters or fewer.
- Run `git diff --cached` before deciding the message.
- Split unrelated changes instead of hiding them under one vague commit.
- Do not include AI signature footers.
